{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738218502,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"id":"prt_e9c44b4ee001vWHmRJ7AAS5IqB","messageID":"msg_e9c44a065001e6aOre36aWfwzo","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","type":"text","text":"I found the live memory surfaces are split between handler entrypoints and lower-level schema/storage helpers. I’m narrowing reads to the specific entrypoints where an automatic/invisible implementation would hook in.","time":{"start":1780738209006,"end":1780738218500},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ba051a4fa2a2d9c016a23e8a100008191b00d9556a3eef3c8","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218551,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_v4XrI6c9jk8aw2JQt0k2GzIs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"001 Aggregator — Shared Feedback Aggregation\"\n3: description: \"Level 2 child packet for the shared TypeScript feedback aggregation reducer used by the feedback reducer consumers.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"009 feedback aggregator\"\n6:   - \"001 aggregator\"\n7:   - \"feedback-aggregation.ts\"\n8:   - \"shared feedback aggregation\"\n9: importance_tier: \"important\"\n10: contextType: \"implementation\"\n11: _memory:\n12:   continuity:\n13:     packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator\"\n14:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n15:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n16:     recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: reuse batch-learning aggregation\"\n17:     next_safe_action: \"Reconcile weighted formula and implement tasks.md\"\n18:     blockers: []\n19:     key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n20:     completion_pct: 0\n21: ---\n22: # Feature Specification: Shared Feedback Aggregation\n23: \n24: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n25: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n30: ## 1. METADATA\n31: \n32: | Field | Value |\n33: |-------|-------|\n34: | **Level** | 2 |\n35: | **Priority** | P0 |\n36: | **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n37: | **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n38: | **Depends On** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-write-safety` |\n39: | **Estimated LOC** | ~70 production LOC |\n40: | **Language** | TypeScript |\n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n46: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n47: \n48: The three learning reducers need a shared interpretation of `feedback_events`. Without a common aggregation layer, each consumer can drift on confidence mapping, weighted-positive math, and window semantics.\n49: \n50: AUDIT 2026-06-05: `batch-learning.ts:195-241` already aggregates `feedback_events`; reuse it. `feedback_events` dependency confirmed present (`feedback-ledger.ts`).\n51: \n52: This child provides the shared foundation aggregation by reusing/extending the existing `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts:195-241` (`aggregateEvents`) rather than creating a duplicate `feedback-aggregation.ts`. The aggregation reads a bounded `{ since, until }` feedback window and returns deterministic per-memory summaries for downstream consumers; only what is missing for those consumers is added on top of the existing reducer.\n53: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n58: ## 3. SCOPE\n59: \n60: ### In Scope\n61: - Reuse/extend `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts:195-241` (`aggregateEvents`) aggregation; avoid a duplicate `feedback-aggregation.ts`.\n62: - Aggregate by `memory_id` (already done by `aggregateEvents`).\n63: - Track strong, medium, weak counts plus sessions, queries, firstSeen, lastSeen, and `weightedHitCount`, adding only the fields not already produced by `aggregateEvents`.\n64: - Reconcile the weighted formula `weightedHitCount = max(0, strong + 0.25 * same_topic_requery - 0.5 * query_reformulated)` with the existing `weightedScore`/`computedBoost` in `batch-learning.ts`: align with or extend the existing weighted formula rather than introduce a parallel one. Keep the non-negative floor.\n65: - Add focused tests for formula behavior and run-twice idempotency.\n66: \n67: ### Out of Scope\n68: - Causal-edge creation.\n69: - Retention mutation or sweep integration.\n70: - ENV_REFERENCE flag documentation.\n71: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n76: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n77: \n78: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n79: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n80: | REQ-001 | Reuse/extend `batch-learning.ts:195-241` (`aggregateEvents`) reading `feedback_events` by `{ since, until }` instead of creating a duplicate `feedback-aggregation.ts`. | API is stable, filters by window, and no parallel aggregator is added. |\n81: | REQ-002 | Aggregate by `memory_id` with strong/medium/weak counts, sessions, queries, and first/last timestamps, adding only fields not already emitted by `aggregateEvents`. | Unit tests cover each field. |\n82: | REQ-003 | Reconcile the weighted-positive formula with the existing `weightedScore`/`computedBoost` in `batch-learning.ts`, keeping the non-negative floor and not introducing a parallel formula. | Tests cover positive-only, negative-only, mixed, and zero-event cases; output aligns with the existing weighted formula. |\n83: | REQ-004 | Reducer output is deterministic and idempotent for identical inputs. | Run-twice test returns equal output. |\n84: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n89: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n90: \n91: - Strict validation passes for this child packet.\n92: - Aggregation unit tests pass.\n93: - Consumers can depend on a single typed summary shape.\n94: - No hot-path mutation is introduced.\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n100: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n101: \n102: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n103: |------|------|--------|------------|\n104: | Dependency | Phase 002 correctness fixes | Consumers should not start before corrected safety preconditions land. | Hard dependency in metadata. |\n105: | Risk | Formula drift | Consumers learn different meanings for positive feedback. | Keep formula centralized here. |\n106: | Risk | Large feedback windows | Memory pressure during aggregation. | Page reads or bounded query windows in implementation. |\n107: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: <!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n112: ## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n113: \n114: - Deterministic output for identical inputs.\n115: - No writes; read-only aggregation only.\n116: - Bounded memory behavior for large event windows.\n117: - Typed return shape for consumer reuse.\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n123: ## 8. EDGE CASES\n124: \n125: - Empty event window returns an empty summary.\n126: - Events without `memory_id` are skipped or reported according to existing ledger semantics.\n127: - Negative signals cannot drive `weightedHitCount` below zero.\n128: - Duplicate events in the same window produce deterministic counts.\n129: <!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n134: ## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n135: \n136: - Whether the reducer should page internally or rely on caller-provided narrow windows is left to implementation, but the public API should remain window-based.\n137: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: <!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n142: ## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n143: \n144: Level 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n150: ## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n151: \n152: - Parent phase map: `../spec.md`\n153: - Preserved legacy context: `legacy-decision-record.md`, `legacy-resource-map.md`\n154: - Consumer children: `../003-causal-reducer/`, `../004-retention-reducer/`\n155: <!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n\n(End of file - total 155 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"001 Aggregator — Shared Feedback Aggregation\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 child packet for the shared TypeScript feedback aggregation reducer used by the feedback reducer consumers.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 feedback aggregator\"\n  - \"001 aggregator\"\n  - \"feedback-aggregation.ts\"\n  - \"shared feedback aggregation\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: reuse batch-learning aggregation\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Reconcile weighted formula and implement tasks.md\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"001 Aggregator — Shared Feedback Aggregation\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 child packet for the shared TypeScript feedback aggregation reducer used by the feedback reducer consumers.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 feedback aggregator\"\n  - \"001 aggregator\"\n  - \"feedback-aggregation.ts\"\n  - \"shared feedback aggregation\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: reuse batch-learning aggregation\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Reconcile weighted formula and implement tasks.md\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0\n---\n# Feature Specification: Shared Feedback Aggregation\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 2 |\n| **Priority** | P0 |\n| **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n| **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n| **Depends On** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-write-safety` |\n| **Estimated LOC** | ~70 production LOC |\n| **Language** | TypeScript |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\nThe three learning reducers need a shared interpretation of `feedback_events`. Without a common aggregation layer, each consumer can drift on confidence mapping, weighted-positive math, and window semantics.\n\nAUDIT 2026-06-05: `batch-learning.ts:195-241` already aggregates `feedback_events`; reuse it. `feedback_events` dependency confirmed present (`feedback-ledger.ts`).\n\nThis child provides the shared foundation aggregation by reusing/extending the existing `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts:195-241` (`aggregateEvents`) rather than creating a duplicate `feedback-aggregation.ts`. The aggregation reads a bounded `{ since, until }` feedback window and returns deterministic per-memory summaries for downstream consumers; only what is missing for those consumers is added on top of the existing reducer.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Reuse/extend `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts:195-241` (`aggregateEvents`) aggregation; avoid a duplicate `feedback-aggregation.ts`.\n- Aggregate by `memory_id` (already done by `aggregateEvents`).\n- Track strong, medium, weak counts plus sessions, queries, firstSeen, lastSeen, and `weightedHitCount`, adding only the fields not already produced by `aggregateEvents`.\n- Reconcile the weighted formula `weightedHitCount = max(0, strong + 0.25 * same_topic_requery - 0.5 * query_reformulated)` with the existing `weightedScore`/`computedBoost` in `batch-learning.ts`: align with or extend the existing weighted formula rather than introduce a parallel one. Keep the non-negative floor.\n- Add focused tests for formula behavior and run-twice idempotency.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Causal-edge creation.\n- Retention mutation or sweep integration.\n- ENV_REFERENCE flag documentation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | Reuse/extend `batch-learning.ts:195-241` (`aggregateEvents`) reading `feedback_events` by `{ since, until }` instead of creating a duplicate `feedback-aggregation.ts`. | API is stable, filters by window, and no parallel aggregator is added. |\n| REQ-002 | Aggregate by `memory_id` with strong/medium/weak counts, sessions, queries, and first/last timestamps, adding only fields not already emitted by `aggregateEvents`. | Unit tests cover each field. |\n| REQ-003 | Reconcile the weighted-positive formula with the existing `weightedScore`/`computedBoost` in `batch-learning.ts`, keeping the non-negative floor and not introducing a parallel formula. | Tests cover positive-only, negative-only, mixed, and zero-event cases; output aligns with the existing weighted formula. |\n| REQ-004 | Reducer output is deterministic and idempotent for identical inputs. | Run-twice test returns equal output. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- Strict validation passes for this child packet.\n- Aggregation unit tests pass.\n- Consumers can depend on a single typed summary shape.\n- No hot-path mutation is introduced.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Dependency | Phase 002 correctness fixes | Consumers should not start before corrected safety preconditions land. | Hard dependency in metadata. |\n| Risk | Formula drift | Consumers learn different meanings for positive feedback. | Keep formula centralized here. |\n| Risk | Large feedback windows | Memory pressure during aggregation. | Page reads or bounded query windows in implementation. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n\n- Deterministic output for identical inputs.\n- No writes; read-only aggregation only.\n- Bounded memory behavior for large event windows.\n- Typed return shape for consumer reuse.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n## 8. EDGE CASES\n\n- Empty event window returns an empty summary.\n- Events without `memory_id` are skipped or reported according to existing ledger semantics.\n- Negative signals cannot drive `weightedHitCount` below zero.\n- Duplicate events in the same window produce deterministic counts.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Whether the reducer should page internally or rely on caller-provided narrow windows is left to implementation, but the public API should remain window-based.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n\nLevel 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n- Parent phase map: `../spec.md`\n- Preserved legacy context: `legacy-decision-record.md`, `legacy-resource-map.md`\n- Consumer children: `../003-causal-reducer/`, `../004-retention-reducer/`\n<!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":155,"totalLines":155,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator/spec.md","time":{"start":1780738218535,"end":1780738218548}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ba051a4fa2a2d9c016a23e8aa797c8191b0aab6db561bf505"}},"id":"prt_e9c44da0a001tj4ZxMK0yskrqH","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c44a065001e6aOre36aWfwzo"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218555,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DG2IwR52qxmy8v0999uXw3QA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"003 Causal Reducer — Session Trace Edges\"\n3: description: \"Level 2 child packet for deferred session-trace causal edge inference.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"009 causal reducer\"\n6:   - \"003 causal reducer\"\n7:   - \"session-trace-causal-reducer.ts\"\n8:   - \"auto-session edges\"\n9: importance_tier: \"important\"\n10: contextType: \"implementation\"\n11: _memory:\n12:   continuity:\n13:     packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer\"\n14:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n15:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n16:     recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: relation-vocab alignment\"\n17:     next_safe_action: \"Implement tasks.md with RELATION_TYPES-aligned coverage targets.\"\n18:     blockers: []\n19:     key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n20:     completion_pct: 0\n21: ---\n22: # Feature Specification: Session-Trace Causal Reducer\n23: \n24: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n25: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n30: ## 1. METADATA\n31: \n32: | Field | Value |\n33: |-------|-------|\n34: | **Level** | 2 |\n35: | **Priority** | P0 |\n36: | **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n37: | **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n38: | **Depends On** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator` |\n39: | **Estimated LOC** | ~265 production LOC |\n40: | **Language** | TypeScript |\n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n46: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n47: \n48: Session traces already record `search_shown` and `result_cited` events, but those signals are never converted into weak causal edges. This child adds a deferred reducer that infers bounded `ENABLED(A -> B)` edges from same-session evidence.\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n54: ## 3. SCOPE\n55: \n56: ### In Scope\n57: - Create `mcp_server/lib/feedback/session-trace-causal-reducer.ts`.\n58: - Read feedback events ordered by `(session_id, timestamp)`.\n59: - For each citation, select 3-5 prior shown sources where `A !== B`.\n60: - Emit `ENABLED` edges at strength `0.3` with `created_by='auto-session'`.\n61:   - AUDIT 2026-06-05: candidate `ENABLED` edges are valid per `RELATION_TYPES` but ABSENT from `DEFAULT_RELATION_TARGETS`; the reducer must validate against `RELATION_TYPES`/schema and align coverage targets before applying the relation floor.\n62: - Preserve manual-edge guard behavior from Phase 002.\n63: - Keep invocation deferred only.\n64: - Add default-off flag `SPECKIT_SESSION_TRACE_CAUSAL_INFERENCE=false`.\n65: \n66: ### Out of Scope\n67: - Live per-event reducer firing.\n68: - Retention learning.\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n74: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n75: \n76: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n77: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n78: | REQ-001 | Add deferred session-trace reducer. | No calls from live feedback logging paths. |\n79: | REQ-002 | Deterministically select prior `search_shown` sources. | Same-query sources preferred; cap enforced. |\n80: | REQ-003 | Emit weak auto-session `ENABLED` edges at strength 0.3. | First-run edge inspection passes. |\n81: | REQ-004 | Preserve manual edges and idempotency. | Existing manual edges are skipped; re-run is bounded. |\n82: | REQ-005 | Feature flag defaults off. | Flag-off creates no edges. |\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n88: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n89: \n90: - Strict validation passes.\n91: - Reducer tests prove source selection, caps, manual protection, idempotency, and flag-off behavior.\n92: - Code review confirms no live invocation path.\n93: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n98: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n99: \n100: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n101: |------|------|--------|------------|\n102: | Dependency | `001-aggregator` | Shared feedback semantics. | Hard dependency. |\n103: | Dependency | Phase 002 | Auto-session cap and manual guard safety. | Parent hard dependency and implementation precheck. |\n104: | Risk | Noisy inferred edges | Ranking pollution. | Deferred only, weak strength, caps, default-off flag. |\n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: <!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n110: ## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n111: \n112: - Deferred invocation only.\n113: - Idempotent per `(session_id, A, B)` pair.\n114: - Enforce existing edge caps.\n115: <!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: <!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n120: ## 8. EDGE CASES\n121: \n122: - Citation with no prior shown source.\n123: - Citation where candidate source equals target.\n124: - Existing manual edge for same pair.\n125: - Re-run over same session.\n126: - Edge cap reached.\n127: <!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n132: ## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n133: \n134: - Whether the explicit maintenance entrypoint is MCP-only or also a CLI command can be decided during implementation.\n135: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: <!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n140: ## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n141: \n142: Level 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n143: <!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: <!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n148: ## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n149: \n150: - `../001-aggregator/spec.md`\n151: - `../005-env-tests-integration/spec.md`\n152: <!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n\n(End of file - total 152 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"003 Causal Reducer — Session Trace Edges\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 child packet for deferred session-trace causal edge inference.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 causal reducer\"\n  - \"003 causal reducer\"\n  - \"session-trace-causal-reducer.ts\"\n  - \"auto-session edges\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: relation-vocab alignment\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Implement tasks.md with RELATION_TYPES-aligned coverage targets.\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"003 Causal Reducer — Session Trace Edges\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 child packet for deferred session-trace causal edge inference.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 causal reducer\"\n  - \"003 causal reducer\"\n  - \"session-trace-causal-reducer.ts\"\n  - \"auto-session edges\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: relation-vocab alignment\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Implement tasks.md with RELATION_TYPES-aligned coverage targets.\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0\n---\n# Feature Specification: Session-Trace Causal Reducer\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 2 |\n| **Priority** | P0 |\n| **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n| **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n| **Depends On** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator` |\n| **Estimated LOC** | ~265 production LOC |\n| **Language** | TypeScript |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\nSession traces already record `search_shown` and `result_cited` events, but those signals are never converted into weak causal edges. This child adds a deferred reducer that infers bounded `ENABLED(A -> B)` edges from same-session evidence.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Create `mcp_server/lib/feedback/session-trace-causal-reducer.ts`.\n- Read feedback events ordered by `(session_id, timestamp)`.\n- For each citation, select 3-5 prior shown sources where `A !== B`.\n- Emit `ENABLED` edges at strength `0.3` with `created_by='auto-session'`.\n  - AUDIT 2026-06-05: candidate `ENABLED` edges are valid per `RELATION_TYPES` but ABSENT from `DEFAULT_RELATION_TARGETS`; the reducer must validate against `RELATION_TYPES`/schema and align coverage targets before applying the relation floor.\n- Preserve manual-edge guard behavior from Phase 002.\n- Keep invocation deferred only.\n- Add default-off flag `SPECKIT_SESSION_TRACE_CAUSAL_INFERENCE=false`.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Live per-event reducer firing.\n- Retention learning.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | Add deferred session-trace reducer. | No calls from live feedback logging paths. |\n| REQ-002 | Deterministically select prior `search_shown` sources. | Same-query sources preferred; cap enforced. |\n| REQ-003 | Emit weak auto-session `ENABLED` edges at strength 0.3. | First-run edge inspection passes. |\n| REQ-004 | Preserve manual edges and idempotency. | Existing manual edges are skipped; re-run is bounded. |\n| REQ-005 | Feature flag defaults off. | Flag-off creates no edges. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- Strict validation passes.\n- Reducer tests prove source selection, caps, manual protection, idempotency, and flag-off behavior.\n- Code review confirms no live invocation path.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Dependency | `001-aggregator` | Shared feedback semantics. | Hard dependency. |\n| Dependency | Phase 002 | Auto-session cap and manual guard safety. | Parent hard dependency and implementation precheck. |\n| Risk | Noisy inferred edges | Ranking pollution. | Deferred only, weak strength, caps, default-off flag. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n\n- Deferred invocation only.\n- Idempotent per `(session_id, A, B)` pair.\n- Enforce existing edge caps.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n## 8. EDGE CASES\n\n- Citation with no prior shown source.\n- Citation where candidate source equals target.\n- Existing manual edge for same pair.\n- Re-run over same session.\n- Edge cap reached.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Whether the explicit maintenance entrypoint is MCP-only or also a CLI command can be decided during implementation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n\nLevel 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n- `../001-aggregator/spec.md`\n- `../005-env-tests-integration/spec.md`\n<!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":152,"totalLines":152,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer/spec.md","time":{"start":1780738218542,"end":1780738218552}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ba051a4fa2a2d9c016a23e8aa799081918196a2a36aae73e5"}},"id":"prt_e9c44da28001wKDoQZnN4mWGor","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c44a065001e6aOre36aWfwzo"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218555,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ct6hS2X2cWJ2Xw4jxMuCi7uG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"004 Retention Reducer — Feedback Retention Learning\"\n3: description: \"Level 2 child packet for learned retention and edge-floor reducer logic.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"009 retention reducer\"\n6:   - \"004 retention reducer\"\n7:   - \"feedback-retention-reducer.ts\"\n8:   - \"edge-tier-basement.ts\"\n9: importance_tier: \"important\"\n10: contextType: \"implementation\"\n11: _memory:\n12:   continuity:\n13:     packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer\"\n14:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n15:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n16:     recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: STATE_LIMITS export precondition\"\n17:     next_safe_action: \"Add STATE_LIMITS production export before implementing tasks.md.\"\n18:     blockers: []\n19:     key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n20:     completion_pct: 0\n21: ---\n22: # Feature Specification: Feedback Retention Reducer\n23: \n24: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n25: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n30: ## 1. METADATA\n31: \n32: | Field | Value |\n33: |-------|-------|\n34: | **Level** | 2 |\n35: | **Priority** | P0 |\n36: | **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n37: | **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n38: | **Depends On** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator` |\n39: | **Estimated LOC** | ~385 production LOC |\n40: | **Language** | TypeScript |\n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n46: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n47: \n48: Retention currently follows rule-based TTL behavior. This child adds a feedback-aware retention reducer that can return `delete`, `extend`, or `protect` decisions while keeping constitutional/critical protection narrow and auditable.\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n54: ## 3. SCOPE\n55: \n56: ### In Scope\n57: - Create `mcp_server/lib/feedback/feedback-retention-reducer.ts`.\n58: - Create `mcp_server/lib/feedback/edge-tier-basement.ts`.\n59:   - PRECONDITION (AUDIT 2026-06-05): `STATE_LIMITS` is currently non-exported (module-local const in `stage4-filter.ts`, only reachable via `__testables`); a production export must be added to `stage4-filter.ts` before this import is possible.\n60: - Consume `001-aggregator` summaries and Phase 002's extended retention row shape.\n61: - Implement `RetentionDecision = delete | extend | protect`.\n62: - Add dry-run shadow path.\n63: - Add feature flags `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_LEARNING=false` and `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_MODE=shadow|active`.\n64: \n65: ### Out of Scope\n66: - Broadening tier floors to auto-derived edges.\n67: - Active mutation before shadow evaluation.\n68: - Causal-edge inference.\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n74: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n75: \n76: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n77: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n78: | REQ-001 | Add retention reducer consuming shared aggregation. | Important positive-feedback records can extend. |\n79: | REQ-002 | Protect constitutional/critical and pinned records. | Expired constitutional rows are not deleted. |\n80: | REQ-003 | Add narrow edge floor helper. | Only manual/authored high-tier pairs or explicit constitutional-chain evidence are floored. |\n81: | REQ-004 | Support `dryRun` shadow decisions without writes. | Dry-run test observes no DB mutation. |\n82: | REQ-005 | Gate active mode behind shadow evaluation and flags. | Flag matrix tests pass. |\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n88: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n89: \n90: - Strict validation passes.\n91: - Decision rules and edge-floor scope tests pass.\n92: - Sweep integration writes audit entries for extend/protect/delete.\n93: - Active mode cannot run without configured flag and eval gate.\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n99: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n100: \n101: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n102: |------|------|--------|------------|\n103: | Dependency | `001-aggregator` | Requires weighted positive summary. | Hard dependency. |\n104: | Dependency | Phase 002 | Requires retention row tier fields. | Parent hard dependency. |\n105: | Risk | Exposure rewarded as value | Retain noisy memories. | Important-tier-only v1 boost and negative signal dampening. |\n106: | Risk | Edge floor protects noise | Bad causal graph durability. | Narrow edge-floor rules. |\n107: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: <!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n112: ## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n113: \n114: - Shadow-first and default-off.\n115: - Auditable decisions.\n116: - No active mutation without gate.\n117: <!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: <!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n122: ## 8. EDGE CASES\n123: \n124: - Constitutional record with expired `delete_after`.\n125: - Pinned record with negative feedback.\n126: - Important record with positive and reformulated signals.\n127: - Normal/temporary record with positive exposure only.\n128: - Auto-derived edge touching one high-tier endpoint.\n129: <!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n134: ## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n135: \n136: - Whether `protect` clears `delete_after` or sets a distant future date remains an implementation choice, but the audit event must record the chosen behavior.\n137: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: <!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n142: ## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n143: \n144: Level 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n150: ## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n151: \n152: - `../001-aggregator/spec.md`\n153: - `../005-env-tests-integration/spec.md`\n154: <!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n\n(End of file - total 154 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"004 Retention Reducer — Feedback Retention Learning\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 child packet for learned retention and edge-floor reducer logic.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 retention reducer\"\n  - \"004 retention reducer\"\n  - \"feedback-retention-reducer.ts\"\n  - \"edge-tier-basement.ts\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: STATE_LIMITS export precondition\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Add STATE_LIMITS production export before implementing tasks.md.\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"004 Retention Reducer — Feedback Retention Learning\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 child packet for learned retention and edge-floor reducer logic.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 retention reducer\"\n  - \"004 retention reducer\"\n  - \"feedback-retention-reducer.ts\"\n  - \"edge-tier-basement.ts\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-05T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied 2026-06-05 audit rescope: STATE_LIMITS export precondition\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Add STATE_LIMITS production export before implementing tasks.md.\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0\n---\n# Feature Specification: Feedback Retention Reducer\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 2 |\n| **Priority** | P0 |\n| **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n| **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n| **Depends On** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator` |\n| **Estimated LOC** | ~385 production LOC |\n| **Language** | TypeScript |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\nRetention currently follows rule-based TTL behavior. This child adds a feedback-aware retention reducer that can return `delete`, `extend`, or `protect` decisions while keeping constitutional/critical protection narrow and auditable.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Create `mcp_server/lib/feedback/feedback-retention-reducer.ts`.\n- Create `mcp_server/lib/feedback/edge-tier-basement.ts`.\n  - PRECONDITION (AUDIT 2026-06-05): `STATE_LIMITS` is currently non-exported (module-local const in `stage4-filter.ts`, only reachable via `__testables`); a production export must be added to `stage4-filter.ts` before this import is possible.\n- Consume `001-aggregator` summaries and Phase 002's extended retention row shape.\n- Implement `RetentionDecision = delete | extend | protect`.\n- Add dry-run shadow path.\n- Add feature flags `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_LEARNING=false` and `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_MODE=shadow|active`.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Broadening tier floors to auto-derived edges.\n- Active mutation before shadow evaluation.\n- Causal-edge inference.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | Add retention reducer consuming shared aggregation. | Important positive-feedback records can extend. |\n| REQ-002 | Protect constitutional/critical and pinned records. | Expired constitutional rows are not deleted. |\n| REQ-003 | Add narrow edge floor helper. | Only manual/authored high-tier pairs or explicit constitutional-chain evidence are floored. |\n| REQ-004 | Support `dryRun` shadow decisions without writes. | Dry-run test observes no DB mutation. |\n| REQ-005 | Gate active mode behind shadow evaluation and flags. | Flag matrix tests pass. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- Strict validation passes.\n- Decision rules and edge-floor scope tests pass.\n- Sweep integration writes audit entries for extend/protect/delete.\n- Active mode cannot run without configured flag and eval gate.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Dependency | `001-aggregator` | Requires weighted positive summary. | Hard dependency. |\n| Dependency | Phase 002 | Requires retention row tier fields. | Parent hard dependency. |\n| Risk | Exposure rewarded as value | Retain noisy memories. | Important-tier-only v1 boost and negative signal dampening. |\n| Risk | Edge floor protects noise | Bad causal graph durability. | Narrow edge-floor rules. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n\n- Shadow-first and default-off.\n- Auditable decisions.\n- No active mutation without gate.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n## 8. EDGE CASES\n\n- Constitutional record with expired `delete_after`.\n- Pinned record with negative feedback.\n- Important record with positive and reformulated signals.\n- Normal/temporary record with positive exposure only.\n- Auto-derived edge touching one high-tier endpoint.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Whether `protect` clears `delete_after` or sets a distant future date remains an implementation choice, but the audit event must record the chosen behavior.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n\nLevel 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n- `../001-aggregator/spec.md`\n- `../005-env-tests-integration/spec.md`\n<!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":154,"totalLines":154,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer/spec.md","time":{"start":1780738218544,"end":1780738218553}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ba051a4fa2a2d9c016a23e8aa79988191a54686345b74a4e1"}},"id":"prt_e9c44da2f001pzPZH5xWzNUzQC","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c44a065001e6aOre36aWfwzo"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218566,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_E0dTqNyLlHV3ovWYgLAmwhy1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"005 Env Tests Integration\"\n3: description: \"Level 2 closeout child for ENV_REFERENCE flags and integration tests across feedback reducer consumers.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"009 env tests integration\"\n6:   - \"005 env tests\"\n7:   - \"feedback reducer integration\"\n8:   - \"ENV_REFERENCE feedback flags\"\n9: importance_tier: \"important\"\n10: contextType: \"implementation\"\n11: _memory:\n12:   continuity:\n13:     packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration\"\n14:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-12T07:20:00Z\"\n15:     last_updated_by: \"cli-codex\"\n16:     recent_action: \"Scaffolded Level 2 child packet\"\n17:     next_safe_action: \"Implement tasks.md\"\n18:     blockers: []\n19:     key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n20:     completion_pct: 0\n21: ---\n22: # Feature Specification: Feedback Reducer Env and Integration Closeout\n23: \n24: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n25: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n30: ## 1. METADATA\n31: \n32: | Field | Value |\n33: |-------|-------|\n34: | **Level** | 2 |\n35: | **Priority** | P0 |\n36: | **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n37: | **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n38: | **Depends On** | `001-aggregator`, `003-causal-reducer`, `004-retention-reducer` |\n39: | **Estimated LOC** | ~100 LOC/docs |\n40: | **Language** | TypeScript + docs |\n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n46: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n47: \n48: The two feedback reducer consumers introduce separate default-off flags and cross-consumer safety expectations. This closeout child verifies that flags are documented and integration behavior remains coherent across the reducers.\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n54: ## 3. SCOPE\n55: \n56: ### In Scope\n57: - Document `SPECKIT_SESSION_TRACE_CAUSAL_INFERENCE`.\n58: - Document `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_LEARNING` and `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_MODE`.\n59: - Add integration tests spanning aggregator plus the two consumers.\n60: - Verify default-off behavior across all consumers.\n61: \n62: ### Out of Scope\n63: - Implementing the consumer internals owned by children 002, 003, and 004.\n64: - Changing Phase 027 root metadata.\n65: - Live rollout decisions beyond documented eval gates.\n66: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n71: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n72: \n73: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n74: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n75: | REQ-001 | Document all feedback reducer flags in `ENV_REFERENCE.md`. | Grep finds all four flag names. |\n76: | REQ-002 | Add integration coverage across aggregator and consumers. | Tests prove flag-off default safety. |\n77: | REQ-003 | Verify active mutation requires configured gates. | Retention active mode blocked without eval gate. |\n78: | REQ-004 | Confirm consumer independence after aggregator. | Tests or docs show 002/003/004 can run independently after 001. |\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n84: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n85: \n86: - Strict validation passes.\n87: - Env docs include every flag and default value.\n88: - Integration tests cover flag-off behavior across all consumers.\n89: - Parent can be considered scaffold-complete after this child lands.\n90: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n95: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n96: \n97: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n98: |------|------|--------|------------|\n99: | Dependency | Children 001-004 | Closeout cannot verify missing modules. | Hard dependency list. |\n100: | Risk | Flag drift | Operators enable wrong behavior. | Single ENV_REFERENCE update with defaults. |\n101: | Risk | Integration gaps | Consumers pass unit tests but fail together. | Cross-consumer integration tests. |\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n107: ## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n108: \n109: - Documentation must state safe defaults.\n110: - Integration tests must avoid live external services.\n111: - Tests should be deterministic and local.\n112: <!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: <!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n117: ## 8. EDGE CASES\n118: \n119: - All flags unset.\n120: - Each consumer flag enabled individually.\n121: - Retention learning enabled with shadow mode.\n122: - Retention active mode requested without eval gate.\n123: <!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n128: ## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n129: \n130: - Exact integration test file layout depends on the final modules from children 002-004.\n131: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: <!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n136: ## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n137: \n138: Level 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n139: <!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: <!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n144: ## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n145: \n146: - `../001-aggregator/spec.md`\n147: - `../003-causal-reducer/spec.md`\n148: - `../004-retention-reducer/spec.md`\n149: <!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n\n(End of file - total 149 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"005 Env Tests Integration\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 closeout child for ENV_REFERENCE flags and integration tests across feedback reducer consumers.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 env tests integration\"\n  - \"005 env tests\"\n  - \"feedback reducer integration\"\n  - \"ENV_REFERENCE feedback flags\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-12T07:20:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"cli-codex\"\n    recent_action: \"Scaffolded Level 2 child packet\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Implement tasks.md\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"005 Env Tests Integration\"\ndescription: \"Level 2 closeout child for ENV_REFERENCE flags and integration tests across feedback reducer consumers.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"009 env tests integration\"\n  - \"005 env tests\"\n  - \"feedback reducer integration\"\n  - \"ENV_REFERENCE feedback flags\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-12T07:20:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"cli-codex\"\n    recent_action: \"Scaffolded Level 2 child packet\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Implement tasks.md\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files: [\"spec.md\", \"plan.md\", \"tasks.md\", \"checklist.md\", \"implementation-summary.md\"]\n    completion_pct: 0\n---\n# Feature Specification: Feedback Reducer Env and Integration Closeout\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 2 |\n| **Priority** | P0 |\n| **Status** | Spec-Scaffolded |\n| **Parent Packet** | `system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers` |\n| **Depends On** | `001-aggregator`, `003-causal-reducer`, `004-retention-reducer` |\n| **Estimated LOC** | ~100 LOC/docs |\n| **Language** | TypeScript + docs |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\nThe two feedback reducer consumers introduce separate default-off flags and cross-consumer safety expectations. This closeout child verifies that flags are documented and integration behavior remains coherent across the reducers.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Document `SPECKIT_SESSION_TRACE_CAUSAL_INFERENCE`.\n- Document `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_LEARNING` and `SPECKIT_FEEDBACK_RETENTION_MODE`.\n- Add integration tests spanning aggregator plus the two consumers.\n- Verify default-off behavior across all consumers.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Implementing the consumer internals owned by children 002, 003, and 004.\n- Changing Phase 027 root metadata.\n- Live rollout decisions beyond documented eval gates.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | Document all feedback reducer flags in `ENV_REFERENCE.md`. | Grep finds all four flag names. |\n| REQ-002 | Add integration coverage across aggregator and consumers. | Tests prove flag-off default safety. |\n| REQ-003 | Verify active mutation requires configured gates. | Retention active mode blocked without eval gate. |\n| REQ-004 | Confirm consumer independence after aggregator. | Tests or docs show 002/003/004 can run independently after 001. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- Strict validation passes.\n- Env docs include every flag and default value.\n- Integration tests cover flag-off behavior across all consumers.\n- Parent can be considered scaffold-complete after this child lands.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Dependency | Children 001-004 | Closeout cannot verify missing modules. | Hard dependency list. |\n| Risk | Flag drift | Operators enable wrong behavior. | Single ENV_REFERENCE update with defaults. |\n| Risk | Integration gaps | Consumers pass unit tests but fail together. | Cross-consumer integration tests. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:nfr -->\n## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n\n- Documentation must state safe defaults.\n- Integration tests must avoid live external services.\n- Tests should be deterministic and local.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:nfr -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n## 8. EDGE CASES\n\n- All flags unset.\n- Each consumer flag enabled individually.\n- Retention learning enabled with shadow mode.\n- Retention active mode requested without eval gate.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:edge-cases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 9. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Exact integration test file layout depends on the final modules from children 002-004.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:complexity -->\n## COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT\n\nLevel 2 is appropriate: this child is implementation-sized, verification-focused, and bounded to one reducer surface.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:complexity -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:related-docs -->\n## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n- `../001-aggregator/spec.md`\n- `../003-causal-reducer/spec.md`\n- `../004-retention-reducer/spec.md`\n<!-- /ANCHOR:related-docs -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":149,"totalLines":149,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration/spec.md","time":{"start":1780738218550,"end":1780738218565}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ba051a4fa2a2d9c016a23e8aa79a0819196dbf350b480d934"}},"id":"prt_e9c44da31001A7WXOmYgH7PZly","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c44a065001e6aOre36aWfwzo"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218569,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mpb0HFKVGvM55WHOhZG7B5Ss","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Memory Crud Update Handler\n3: // ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: \n5: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6:    IMPORTS\n7: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n8: \n9: import { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n10: import { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\n11: import { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\n12: import * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\n13: import type { UpdateMemoryParams } from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\n14: import * as embeddings from '../lib/providers/embeddings.js';\n15: import * as bm25Index from '../lib/search/bm25-index.js';\n16: import { VALID_TIERS, isValidTier } from '../lib/scoring/importance-tiers.js';\n17: import { MemoryError, ErrorCodes } from '../lib/errors.js';\n18: import * as mutationLedger from '../lib/storage/mutation-ledger.js';\n19: import { runInTransaction } from '../lib/storage/transaction-manager.js';\n20: import { createMCPSuccessResponse, createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\n21: import {\n22:   buildGovernanceLogicalKey,\n23:   recordTierDowngradeAudit,\n24: } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\n25: import { isConstitutionalPath } from '../lib/utils/index-scope.js';\n26: import { toErrorMessage } from '../utils/index.js';\n27: \n28: import { recordHistory } from '../lib/storage/history.js';\n29: import { appendMutationLedgerSafe, getMemoryHashSnapshot } from './memory-crud-utils.js';\n30: import { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\n31: import { buildMutationHookFeedback } from '../hooks/mutation-feedback.js';\n32: \n33: import type { MCPResponse } from './types.js';\n34: import type { UpdateArgs } from './memory-crud-types.js';\n35: \n36: // Feature catalog: Memory metadata update (memory_update)\n37: // Feature catalog: Validation feedback (memory_validate)\n38: // Feature catalog: Transaction wrappers on mutation handlers\n39: // Feature catalog: Per-memory history log\n40: \n41: \n42: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n43:    CORE LOGIC\n44: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n45: \n46: /** Handle memory_update tool -- updates metadata fields and optionally regenerates embeddings. */\n47: async function handleMemoryUpdate(args: UpdateArgs): Promise<MCPResponse> {\n48:   await ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized('handler:memory_update');\n49:   // Generate requestId for incident correlation in error responses\n50:   const requestId = randomUUID();\n51:   await checkDatabaseUpdated();\n52: \n53:   const {\n54:     id,\n55:     title,\n56:     triggerPhrases,\n57:     importanceWeight,\n58:     importanceTier,\n59:     allowPartialUpdate = false,\n60:   } = args;\n61: \n62:   if (typeof id !== 'number') {\n63:     throw new MemoryError(ErrorCodes.MISSING_REQUIRED_PARAM, 'id is required', { param: 'id' });\n64:   }\n65: \n66:   if (importanceWeight !== undefined && (typeof importanceWeight !== 'number' || importanceWeight < 0 || importanceWeight > 1)) {\n67:     throw new MemoryError(\n68:       ErrorCodes.INVALID_PARAMETER,\n69:       'importanceWeight must be a number between 0 and 1',\n70:       { param: 'importanceWeight', value: importanceWeight }\n71:     );\n72:   }\n73: \n74:   if (importanceTier !== undefined && !isValidTier(importanceTier)) {\n75:     throw new MemoryError(\n76:       ErrorCodes.INVALID_PARAMETER,\n77:       `Invalid importance tier: ${importanceTier}. Valid tiers: ${VALID_TIERS.join(', ')}`,\n78:       { param: 'importanceTier', value: importanceTier }\n79:     );\n80:   }\n81: \n82:   const existing = vectorIndex.getMemory(id);\n83:   if (!existing) {\n84:     throw new MemoryError(ErrorCodes.FILE_NOT_FOUND, `Memory not found: ${id}`, { id });\n85:   }\n86: \n87:   const database = vectorIndex.getDb();\n88:   const priorSnapshot = getMemoryHashSnapshot(database, id);\n89: \n90:   const updateParams: UpdateMemoryParams = { id };\n91:   if (title !== undefined) updateParams.title = title;\n92:   if (triggerPhrases !== undefined) updateParams.triggerPhrases = triggerPhrases;\n93:   if (importanceWeight !== undefined) updateParams.importanceWeight = importanceWeight;\n94:   if (importanceTier !== undefined) updateParams.importanceTier = importanceTier;\n95: \n96:   let embeddingRegenerated = false;\n97:   let embeddingMarkedForReindex = false;\n98:   let embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite = false;\n99:   let mutationLedgerWarning: string | null = null;\n100: \n101:   if (title !== undefined && title !== existing.title) {\n102:     console.error(`[memory-update] Title changed, regenerating embedding for memory ${id} [requestId=${requestId}]`);\n103:     let newEmbedding: Float32Array | null = null;\n104: \n105:     try {\n106:       // Embed title + content_text, not title alone.\n107:       // This produces better semantic embeddings that capture the full memory context.\n108:       const contentText = existing.content_text || '';\n109:       const embeddingInput = contentText ? `${title}\\n\\n${contentText}` : title;\n110:       newEmbedding = await embeddings.generateDocumentEmbedding(embeddingInput);\n111:     } catch (err: unknown) {\n112:       const message = toErrorMessage(err);\n113:       if (allowPartialUpdate) {\n114:         console.warn(`[memory-update] Embedding regeneration failed, marking for re-index [requestId=${requestId}]: ${message}`);\n115:         embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite = true;\n116:         embeddingMarkedForReindex = true;\n117:       } else {\n118:         console.error(`[memory-update] Embedding regeneration failed, rolling back update [requestId=${requestId}]: ${message}`);\n119:         throw new MemoryError(\n120:           ErrorCodes.EMBEDDING_FAILED,\n121:           'Embedding regeneration failed, update rolled back. No changes were made.',\n122:           { originalError: message, memoryId: id }\n123:         );\n124:       }\n125:     }\n126: \n127:     if (newEmbedding) {\n128:       updateParams.embedding = newEmbedding;\n129:       embeddingRegenerated = true;\n130:     } else if (!embeddingMarkedForReindex) {\n131:       if (allowPartialUpdate) {\n132:         console.warn('[memory-update] Embedding returned null, marking for re-index');\n133:         embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite = true;\n134:         embeddingMarkedForReindex = true;\n135:       } else {\n136:         throw new MemoryError(\n137:           ErrorCodes.EMBEDDING_FAILED,\n138:           'Failed to regenerate embedding (null result), update rolled back. No changes were made.',\n139:           { memoryId: id }\n140:         );\n141:       }\n142:     }\n143:   }\n144: \n145:   // transaction wrapper — wraps all synchronous mutation steps (DB update,\n146:   // Cache invalidation, BM25 re-index, ledger append) in a single transaction for atomicity.\n147:   // Embedding generation (async) runs before this block; its result feeds into updateParams.\n148:   const fields = Object.keys(updateParams).filter((key) => key !== 'id' && key !== 'embedding');\n149: \n150:   if (database) {\n151:     runInTransaction(database, () => {\n152:       if (embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite) {\n153:         vectorIndex.updateEmbeddingStatus(id, 'pending');\n154:       }\n155: \n156:       vectorIndex.updateMemory(updateParams);\n157: \n158:       if (importanceTier !== undefined) {\n159:         const updated = vectorIndex.getMemory(id) as (Record<string, unknown> | null);\n160:         const previousTier = typeof existing.importance_tier === 'string'\n161:           ? existing.importance_tier\n162:           : undefined;\n163:         const nextTier = typeof updated?.importance_tier === 'string'\n164:           ? updated.importance_tier\n165:           : (previousTier ?? importanceTier);\n166:         const guardPathCandidate = [\n167:           updated?.canonical_file_path,\n168:           updated?.file_path,\n169:           existing.canonical_file_path,\n170:           existing.file_path,\n171:         ].find((value) => typeof value === 'string' && value.length > 0);\n172:         const guardPath = typeof guardPathCandidate === 'string' ? guardPathCandidate : null;\n173: \n174:         if (\n175:           guardPath\n176:           && !isConstitutionalPath(guardPath)\n177:           && previousTier === 'constitutional'\n178:           && nextTier !== 'constitutional'\n179:         ) {\n180:           try {\n181:             const specFolder = typeof updated?.spec_folder === 'string'\n182:               ? updated.spec_folder\n183:               : (typeof existing.spec_folder === 'string' ? existing.spec_folder : null);\n184:             const anchorIdCandidate = typeof updated?.anchor_id === 'string'\n185:               ? updated.anchor_id\n186:               : (typeof existing.anchor_id === 'string' ? existing.anchor_id : null);\n187:             const anchorId = typeof anchorIdCandidate === 'string' ? anchorIdCandidate : null;\n188:             const updatedFilePath = typeof updated?.file_path === 'string'\n189:               ? updated.file_path\n190:               : (typeof existing.file_path === 'string' ? existing.file_path : null);\n191:             const updatedCanonicalFilePath = typeof updated?.canonical_file_path === 'string'\n192:               ? updated.canonical_file_path\n193:               : (typeof existing.canonical_file_path === 'string' ? existing.canonical_file_path : null);\n194:             recordTierDowngradeAudit(database, {\n195:               memoryId: id,\n196:               logicalKey: buildGovernanceLogicalKey(specFolder, guardPath, anchorId),\n197:               requestedTier: importanceTier,\n198:               previousTier,\n199:               nextTier,\n200:               source: 'memory_update',\n201:               filePath: updatedFilePath,\n202:               canonicalFilePath: updatedCanonicalFilePath,\n203:             });\n204:           } catch (error: unknown) {\n205:             console.warn(\n206:               `[memory-crud-update] governance_audit insert failed for memory ${id}: ${toErrorMessage(error)}`,\n207:             );\n208:           }\n209:         }\n210:       }\n211: \n212:       // BM25 index stores title + trigger phrases; must re-index when either changes\n213:       // so keyword search reflects the updated content.\n214:       // BM25 re-index failure now rolls back the transaction when the index is operational.\n215:       // Infrastructure failures (BM25 not available, DB missing prepare) are non-fatal warnings.\n216:       if ((updateParams.title !== undefined || updateParams.triggerPhrases !== undefined) && bm25Index.isBm25Enabled()) {\n217:         try {\n218:           const bm25Idx = bm25Index.getIndex();\n219:           const row = database.prepare(\n220:             'SELECT title, content_text, trigger_phrases, file_path FROM memory_index WHERE id = ?'\n221:           ).get(id) as { title: string | null; content_text: string | null; trigger_phrases: string | null; file_path: string | null } | undefined;\n222:           if (row) {\n223:             const text = bm25Index.buildBm25DocumentText(row);\n224:             if (text.trim()) {\n225:               bm25Idx.addDocument(String(id), text);\n226:             }\n227:           }\n228:         } catch (e: unknown) {\n229:           const bm25ErrMsg = e instanceof Error ? e.message : String(e);\n230:           // Distinguish infrastructure failures from data failures.\n231:           // Infrastructure failures mean the BM25 subsystem is unavailable or torn down —\n232:           // These are non-fatal warnings. Data failures mean the index IS operational but rejected\n233:           // The input — those must re-throw to roll back the transaction.\n234:           const isBm25InfraFailure = (msg: string): boolean =>\n235:             msg.includes('not a function') ||\n236:             msg.includes('not initialized') ||\n237:             msg.includes('Cannot read properties') ||\n238:             msg.includes('is not defined') ||\n239:             msg.includes('database is closed') ||\n240:             msg.includes('no such table');\n241:           if (isBm25InfraFailure(bm25ErrMsg)) {\n242:             console.warn(`[memory-crud-update] BM25 infrastructure unavailable, skipping re-index [requestId=${requestId}]: ${bm25ErrMsg}`);\n243:           } else {\n244:             console.error(`[memory-crud-update] BM25 re-index failed, rolling back update [requestId=${requestId}]: ${bm25ErrMsg}`);\n245:             throw new Error(`BM25 re-index failed: ${bm25ErrMsg}`);\n246:           }\n247:         }\n248:       }\n249: \n250:       // Record UPDATE history after successful mutation\n251:       try {\n252:         recordHistory(\n253:           id, 'UPDATE',\n254:           existing.title ?? null,\n255:           updateParams.title ?? existing.title ?? null,\n256:           'mcp:memory_update'\n257:         );\n258:       } catch (_histErr: unknown) {\n259:         // History recording is best-effort\n260:       }\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 361. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Crud Update Handler\n// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   IMPORTS\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\nimport { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\nimport * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport type { UpdateMemoryParams } from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport * as embeddings from '../lib/providers/embeddings.js';\nimport * as bm25Index from '../lib/search/bm25-index.js';\nimport { VALID_TIERS, isValidTier } from '../lib/scoring/importance-tiers.js';\nimport { MemoryError, ErrorCodes } from '../lib/errors.js';\nimport * as mutationLedger from '../lib/storage/mutation-ledger.js';\nimport { runInTransaction } from '../lib/storage/transaction-manager.js';\nimport { createMCPSuccessResponse, createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts","text":"// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Crud Update Handler\n// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   IMPORTS\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\nimport { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\nimport * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport type { UpdateMemoryParams } from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport * as embeddings from '../lib/providers/embeddings.js';\nimport * as bm25Index from '../lib/search/bm25-index.js';\nimport { VALID_TIERS, isValidTier } from '../lib/scoring/importance-tiers.js';\nimport { MemoryError, ErrorCodes } from '../lib/errors.js';\nimport * as mutationLedger from '../lib/storage/mutation-ledger.js';\nimport { runInTransaction } from '../lib/storage/transaction-manager.js';\nimport { createMCPSuccessResponse, createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\nimport {\n  buildGovernanceLogicalKey,\n  recordTierDowngradeAudit,\n} from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\nimport { isConstitutionalPath } from '../lib/utils/index-scope.js';\nimport { toErrorMessage } from '../utils/index.js';\n\nimport { recordHistory } from '../lib/storage/history.js';\nimport { appendMutationLedgerSafe, getMemoryHashSnapshot } from './memory-crud-utils.js';\nimport { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\nimport { buildMutationHookFeedback } from '../hooks/mutation-feedback.js';\n\nimport type { MCPResponse } from './types.js';\nimport type { UpdateArgs } from './memory-crud-types.js';\n\n// Feature catalog: Memory metadata update (memory_update)\n// Feature catalog: Validation feedback (memory_validate)\n// Feature catalog: Transaction wrappers on mutation handlers\n// Feature catalog: Per-memory history log\n\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   CORE LOGIC\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\n/** Handle memory_update tool -- updates metadata fields and optionally regenerates embeddings. */\nasync function handleMemoryUpdate(args: UpdateArgs): Promise<MCPResponse> {\n  await ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized('handler:memory_update');\n  // Generate requestId for incident correlation in error responses\n  const requestId = randomUUID();\n  await checkDatabaseUpdated();\n\n  const {\n    id,\n    title,\n    triggerPhrases,\n    importanceWeight,\n    importanceTier,\n    allowPartialUpdate = false,\n  } = args;\n\n  if (typeof id !== 'number') {\n    throw new MemoryError(ErrorCodes.MISSING_REQUIRED_PARAM, 'id is required', { param: 'id' });\n  }\n\n  if (importanceWeight !== undefined && (typeof importanceWeight !== 'number' || importanceWeight < 0 || importanceWeight > 1)) {\n    throw new MemoryError(\n      ErrorCodes.INVALID_PARAMETER,\n      'importanceWeight must be a number between 0 and 1',\n      { param: 'importanceWeight', value: importanceWeight }\n    );\n  }\n\n  if (importanceTier !== undefined && !isValidTier(importanceTier)) {\n    throw new MemoryError(\n      ErrorCodes.INVALID_PARAMETER,\n      `Invalid importance tier: ${importanceTier}. Valid tiers: ${VALID_TIERS.join(', ')}`,\n      { param: 'importanceTier', value: importanceTier }\n    );\n  }\n\n  const existing = vectorIndex.getMemory(id);\n  if (!existing) {\n    throw new MemoryError(ErrorCodes.FILE_NOT_FOUND, `Memory not found: ${id}`, { id });\n  }\n\n  const database = vectorIndex.getDb();\n  const priorSnapshot = getMemoryHashSnapshot(database, id);\n\n  const updateParams: UpdateMemoryParams = { id };\n  if (title !== undefined) updateParams.title = title;\n  if (triggerPhrases !== undefined) updateParams.triggerPhrases = triggerPhrases;\n  if (importanceWeight !== undefined) updateParams.importanceWeight = importanceWeight;\n  if (importanceTier !== undefined) updateParams.importanceTier = importanceTier;\n\n  let embeddingRegenerated = false;\n  let embeddingMarkedForReindex = false;\n  let embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite = false;\n  let mutationLedgerWarning: string | null = null;\n\n  if (title !== undefined && title !== existing.title) {\n    console.error(`[memory-update] Title changed, regenerating embedding for memory ${id} [requestId=${requestId}]`);\n    let newEmbedding: Float32Array | null = null;\n\n    try {\n      // Embed title + content_text, not title alone.\n      // This produces better semantic embeddings that capture the full memory context.\n      const contentText = existing.content_text || '';\n      const embeddingInput = contentText ? `${title}\\n\\n${contentText}` : title;\n      newEmbedding = await embeddings.generateDocumentEmbedding(embeddingInput);\n    } catch (err: unknown) {\n      const message = toErrorMessage(err);\n      if (allowPartialUpdate) {\n        console.warn(`[memory-update] Embedding regeneration failed, marking for re-index [requestId=${requestId}]: ${message}`);\n        embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite = true;\n        embeddingMarkedForReindex = true;\n      } else {\n        console.error(`[memory-update] Embedding regeneration failed, rolling back update [requestId=${requestId}]: ${message}`);\n        throw new MemoryError(\n          ErrorCodes.EMBEDDING_FAILED,\n          'Embedding regeneration failed, update rolled back. No changes were made.',\n          { originalError: message, memoryId: id }\n        );\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (newEmbedding) {\n      updateParams.embedding = newEmbedding;\n      embeddingRegenerated = true;\n    } else if (!embeddingMarkedForReindex) {\n      if (allowPartialUpdate) {\n        console.warn('[memory-update] Embedding returned null, marking for re-index');\n        embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite = true;\n        embeddingMarkedForReindex = true;\n      } else {\n        throw new MemoryError(\n          ErrorCodes.EMBEDDING_FAILED,\n          'Failed to regenerate embedding (null result), update rolled back. No changes were made.',\n          { memoryId: id }\n        );\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // transaction wrapper — wraps all synchronous mutation steps (DB update,\n  // Cache invalidation, BM25 re-index, ledger append) in a single transaction for atomicity.\n  // Embedding generation (async) runs before this block; its result feeds into updateParams.\n  const fields = Object.keys(updateParams).filter((key) => key !== 'id' && key !== 'embedding');\n\n  if (database) {\n    runInTransaction(database, () => {\n      if (embeddingStatusNeedsPendingWrite) {\n        vectorIndex.updateEmbeddingStatus(id, 'pending');\n      }\n\n      vectorIndex.updateMemory(updateParams);\n\n      if (importanceTier !== undefined) {\n        const updated = vectorIndex.getMemory(id) as (Record<string, unknown> | null);\n        const previousTier = typeof existing.importance_tier === 'string'\n          ? existing.importance_tier\n          : undefined;\n        const nextTier = typeof updated?.importance_tier === 'string'\n          ? updated.importance_tier\n          : (previousTier ?? importanceTier);\n        const guardPathCandidate = [\n          updated?.canonical_file_path,\n          updated?.file_path,\n          existing.canonical_file_path,\n          existing.file_path,\n        ].find((value) => typeof value === 'string' && value.length > 0);\n        const guardPath = typeof guardPathCandidate === 'string' ? guardPathCandidate : null;\n\n        if (\n          guardPath\n          && !isConstitutionalPath(guardPath)\n          && previousTier === 'constitutional'\n          && nextTier !== 'constitutional'\n        ) {\n          try {\n            const specFolder = typeof updated?.spec_folder === 'string'\n              ? updated.spec_folder\n              : (typeof existing.spec_folder === 'string' ? existing.spec_folder : null);\n            const anchorIdCandidate = typeof updated?.anchor_id === 'string'\n              ? updated.anchor_id\n              : (typeof existing.anchor_id === 'string' ? existing.anchor_id : null);\n            const anchorId = typeof anchorIdCandidate === 'string' ? anchorIdCandidate : null;\n            const updatedFilePath = typeof updated?.file_path === 'string'\n              ? updated.file_path\n              : (typeof existing.file_path === 'string' ? existing.file_path : null);\n            const updatedCanonicalFilePath = typeof updated?.canonical_file_path === 'string'\n              ? updated.canonical_file_path\n              : (typeof existing.canonical_file_path === 'string' ? existing.canonical_file_path : null);\n            recordTierDowngradeAudit(database, {\n              memoryId: id,\n              logicalKey: buildGovernanceLogicalKey(specFolder, guardPath, anchorId),\n              requestedTier: importanceTier,\n              previousTier,\n              nextTier,\n              source: 'memory_update',\n              filePath: updatedFilePath,\n              canonicalFilePath: updatedCanonicalFilePath,\n            });\n          } catch (error: unknown) {\n            console.warn(\n              `[memory-crud-update] governance_audit insert failed for memory ${id}: ${toErrorMessage(error)}`,\n            );\n          }\n        }\n      }\n\n      // BM25 index stores title + trigger phrases; must re-index when either changes\n      // so keyword search reflects the updated content.\n      // BM25 re-index failure now rolls back the transaction when the index is operational.\n      // Infrastructure failures (BM25 not available, DB missing prepare) are non-fatal warnings.\n      if ((updateParams.title !== undefined || updateParams.triggerPhrases !== undefined) && bm25Index.isBm25Enabled()) {\n        try {\n          const bm25Idx = bm25Index.getIndex();\n          const row = database.prepare(\n            'SELECT title, content_text, trigger_phrases, file_path FROM memory_index WHERE id = ?'\n          ).get(id) as { title: string | null; content_text: string | null; trigger_phrases: string | null; file_path: string | null } | undefined;\n          if (row) {\n            const text = bm25Index.buildBm25DocumentText(row);\n            if (text.trim()) {\n              bm25Idx.addDocument(String(id), text);\n            }\n          }\n        } catch (e: unknown) {\n          const bm25ErrMsg = e instanceof Error ? e.message : String(e);\n          // Distinguish infrastructure failures from data failures.\n          // Infrastructure failures mean the BM25 subsystem is unavailable or torn down —\n          // These are non-fatal warnings. Data failures mean the index IS operational but rejected\n          // The input — those must re-throw to roll back the transaction.\n          const isBm25InfraFailure = (msg: string): boolean =>\n            msg.includes('not a function') ||\n            msg.includes('not initialized') ||\n            msg.includes('Cannot read properties') ||\n            msg.includes('is not defined') ||\n            msg.includes('database is closed') ||\n            msg.includes('no such table');\n          if (isBm25InfraFailure(bm25ErrMsg)) {\n            console.warn(`[memory-crud-update] BM25 infrastructure unavailable, skipping re-index [requestId=${requestId}]: ${bm25ErrMsg}`);\n          } else {\n            console.error(`[memory-crud-update] BM25 re-index failed, rolling back update [requestId=${requestId}]: ${bm25ErrMsg}`);\n            throw new Error(`BM25 re-index failed: ${bm25ErrMsg}`);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Record UPDATE history after successful mutation\n      try {\n        recordHistory(\n          id, 'UPDATE',\n          existing.title ?? null,\n          updateParams.title ?? existing.title ?? null,\n          'mcp:memory_update'\n        );\n      } catch (_histErr: unknown) {\n        // History recording is best-effort\n      }","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":361,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts","time":{"start":1780738218563,"end":1780738218568}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ba051a4fa2a2d9c016a23e8aa79b08191a17457340a5794d8"}},"id":"prt_e9c44da3d001pBrLc0oX87skDR","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c44a065001e6aOre36aWfwzo"}}
