{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738336688,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"id":"prt_e9c468c7b001JQtliIZs1GV6ra","messageID":"msg_e9c467dcd001xmgOSJv6XvGnpX","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","type":"text","text":"The stale/status audit has a concrete current risk: `memory_search` forces `includeArchived=false`, while the FTS channel explicitly filters out `importance_tier='deprecated'`. The audit should verify whether vector, BM25, FTS, canonical filtering, and source-contract reporting all treat deprecated/status rows consistently instead of silently dropping relevant history.","time":{"start":1780738329724,"end":1780738336685},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_015f10284b7540fd016a23e919b6ec8191aeba9a7512396c4b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738336751,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sqRu6SjUwfZbYUlR6QWH7S1G","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts","offset":150,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n150:  * Uses SQLite FTS5's built-in bm25() ranking function with\n151:  * per-column weights instead of the default `rank` pseudo-column.\n152:  * This gives title matches 10x weight, trigger_phrases 5x, etc.\n153:  *\n154:  * @param db - SQLite database connection\n155:  * @param query - Raw search query (will be sanitized)\n156:  * @param options - Search options (limit, specFolder, includeArchived)\n157:  * @returns Array of results with BM25 scores (higher = better)\n158:  * @example\n159:  * ```ts\n160:  * const rows = fts5Bm25Search(db, 'memory search', { limit: 10 });\n161:  * ```\n162:  */\n163: function fts5Bm25Search(\n164:   db: Database.Database,\n165:   query: string,\n166:   options: FtsBm25Options = {}\n167: ): FtsBm25Result[] {\n168:   const { limit = 20, specFolder, includeArchived = false } = options;\n169:   void includeArchived;\n170: \n171:   // Sanitize via shared tokenizer, then join quoted terms with OR for recall.\n172:   const sanitized = normalizeLexicalQueryTokens(query).fts;\n173: \n174:   if (!sanitized) {\n175:     setLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot(probeFts5Capability(db));\n176:     return [];\n177:   }\n178: \n179:   const folderFilter = specFolder\n180:     ? \"AND (m.spec_folder = ? OR m.spec_folder LIKE ? || '/%')\"\n181:     : '';\n182:   const deprecatedTierFilter =\n183:     \"AND (m.importance_tier IS NULL OR m.importance_tier != 'deprecated')\";\n184: \n185:   const params: (string | number)[] = specFolder\n186:     ? [sanitized, specFolder, specFolder, limit]\n187:     : [sanitized, limit];\n188: \n189:   // Bm25() returns negative scores (lower = better), so we negate\n190:   // To produce positive scores where higher = better match.\n191:   const [w0, w1, w2, w3] = BM25_FTS5_WEIGHTS;\n192:   const sql = `\n193:     SELECT m.*, -bm25(memory_fts, ${w0}, ${w1}, ${w2}, ${w3}) AS fts_score\n194:     FROM memory_fts\n195:     JOIN memory_index m ON m.id = memory_fts.rowid\n196:     WHERE memory_fts MATCH ?\n197:       ${folderFilter}\n198:       ${deprecatedTierFilter}\n199:     ORDER BY fts_score DESC\n200:     LIMIT ?\n201:   `;\n202: \n203:   const capability = probeFts5Capability(db);\n204:   setLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot(capability);\n205:   if (capability.fallbackState !== 'ok') {\n206:     console.warn(`[sqlite-fts] FTS5 unavailable (${capability.fallbackState}); returning empty lexical lane results`);\n207:     return [];\n208:   }\n209: \n210:   try {\n211:     const rows = (db.prepare(sql) as Database.Statement).all(\n212:       ...params\n213:     ) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n214: \n215:     const normalizedRows = rows.map(row => ({\n216:       ...row,\n217:       id: row.id as number,\n218:       fts_score: (row.fts_score as number) || 0,\n219:     }));\n\n(Showing lines 150-219 of 294. Use offset=220 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":" * Uses SQLite FTS5's built-in bm25() ranking function with\n * per-column weights instead of the default `rank` pseudo-column.\n * This gives title matches 10x weight, trigger_phrases 5x, etc.\n *\n * @param db - SQLite database connection\n * @param query - Raw search query (will be sanitized)\n * @param options - Search options (limit, specFolder, includeArchived)\n * @returns Array of results with BM25 scores (higher = better)\n * @example\n * ```ts\n * const rows = fts5Bm25Search(db, 'memory search', { limit: 10 });\n * ```\n */\nfunction fts5Bm25Search(\n  db: Database.Database,\n  query: string,\n  options: FtsBm25Options = {}\n): FtsBm25Result[] {\n  const { limit = 20, specFolder, includeArchived = false } = options;\n  void includeArchived;","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts","text":" * Uses SQLite FTS5's built-in bm25() ranking function with\n * per-column weights instead of the default `rank` pseudo-column.\n * This gives title matches 10x weight, trigger_phrases 5x, etc.\n *\n * @param db - SQLite database connection\n * @param query - Raw search query (will be sanitized)\n * @param options - Search options (limit, specFolder, includeArchived)\n * @returns Array of results with BM25 scores (higher = better)\n * @example\n * ```ts\n * const rows = fts5Bm25Search(db, 'memory search', { limit: 10 });\n * ```\n */\nfunction fts5Bm25Search(\n  db: Database.Database,\n  query: string,\n  options: FtsBm25Options = {}\n): FtsBm25Result[] {\n  const { limit = 20, specFolder, includeArchived = false } = options;\n  void includeArchived;\n\n  // Sanitize via shared tokenizer, then join quoted terms with OR for recall.\n  const sanitized = normalizeLexicalQueryTokens(query).fts;\n\n  if (!sanitized) {\n    setLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot(probeFts5Capability(db));\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  const folderFilter = specFolder\n    ? \"AND (m.spec_folder = ? OR m.spec_folder LIKE ? || '/%')\"\n    : '';\n  const deprecatedTierFilter =\n    \"AND (m.importance_tier IS NULL OR m.importance_tier != 'deprecated')\";\n\n  const params: (string | number)[] = specFolder\n    ? [sanitized, specFolder, specFolder, limit]\n    : [sanitized, limit];\n\n  // Bm25() returns negative scores (lower = better), so we negate\n  // To produce positive scores where higher = better match.\n  const [w0, w1, w2, w3] = BM25_FTS5_WEIGHTS;\n  const sql = `\n    SELECT m.*, -bm25(memory_fts, ${w0}, ${w1}, ${w2}, ${w3}) AS fts_score\n    FROM memory_fts\n    JOIN memory_index m ON m.id = memory_fts.rowid\n    WHERE memory_fts MATCH ?\n      ${folderFilter}\n      ${deprecatedTierFilter}\n    ORDER BY fts_score DESC\n    LIMIT ?\n  `;\n\n  const capability = probeFts5Capability(db);\n  setLastLexicalCapabilitySnapshot(capability);\n  if (capability.fallbackState !== 'ok') {\n    console.warn(`[sqlite-fts] FTS5 unavailable (${capability.fallbackState}); returning empty lexical lane results`);\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const rows = (db.prepare(sql) as Database.Statement).all(\n      ...params\n    ) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n\n    const normalizedRows = rows.map(row => ({\n      ...row,\n      id: row.id as number,\n      fts_score: (row.fts_score as number) || 0,\n    }));","lineStart":150,"lineEnd":219,"totalLines":294,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts","time":{"start":1780738336722,"end":1780738336747}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_015f10284b7540fd016a23e920a8588191bba085569d15d8d9"}},"id":"prt_e9c46a7af0011bXdl8s4HzgR74","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c467dcd001xmgOSJv6XvGnpX"}}
