vider from memory_health at start and end of run.\n\n  Line 86: - Optional: memory_health \"lazy_warmup_completed\" timing to separate cold-start from steady-state.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/24--local-llm-query-intelligence/specificity-ladder.md:\n  Line 4: audited_post_018: true\n\n  Line 87: - Active provider from memory_health.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/24--local-llm-query-intelligence/paraphrase-recall.md:\n  Line 4: audited_post_018: true\n\n  Line 91: - Note which provider was active (ollama vs hf-local) from `memory_health`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/24--local-llm-query-intelligence/synonymy-across-vocabularies.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Verifies that domain-jargon and plain-language queries surface the same canonical results. Uses live memory IDs and code paths so stale fixture targets do not masquerade as embedder failures.\"\n\n  Line 4: audited_post_018: true\n\n  Line 71: - Pair A: top-5 should both surface live memory ID `7007`, the current successor for the stale `4437` / `5143` V-rule checklist lineage. Expected overlap >= 25% after live-target visibility is confirmed.\n\n  Line 72: - Pair B: top-5 should both surface live memory ID `8048`, the current successor for stale ID `4400`. Expected overlap >= 25% after live-target visibility is confirmed.\n\n  Line 80: - Active provider from `memory_health`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/24--local-llm-query-intelligence/llm-made-memory-recall.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"The local LLM has been storing memories through generate-context.js + memory_save. Validate that deterministic paraphrases of LLM-stored memories surface their exact source IDs without stale corpus rows polluting the result.\"\n\n  Line 4: audited_post_018: true\n\n  Line 76: - Active provider from memory_health.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/24--local-llm-query-intelligence/disambiguation-under-context.md:\n  Line 4: audited_post_018: true\n\n  Line 92: - Active provider from memory_health.\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 1566 matches (1466 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":1566,"truncated":true},"title":"doctor memory|/doctor memory|memory_health|memory_embedding_reconcile|retention_sweep|audit|stale|deprecated","time":{"start":1780738336740,"end":1780738336811}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_015f10284b7540fd016a23e920a884819189ed57e7e6931ae4"}},"id":"prt_e9c46a7e3001mRREjinIjGH9BC","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","messageID":"msg_e9c467dcd001xmgOSJv6XvGnpX"}}
