{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738430621,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","part":{"id":"prt_e9c471e220010B8cE1HtyWnsfY","messageID":"msg_e9c46ab14001DeJOVh06KB233R","sessionID":"ses_163bcc508ffey1OIiwa9Lcz6qq","type":"text","text":"## Integration map\n\n| Item | Target file/surface | Change type | User-visible? | Automatable? | Notes |\n|---|---|---:|---|---|---|\n| 010/P1 T1 idempotency receipts for retryable `memory_save` / `memory_update` | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/dedup.ts` | New schema + handler edits | Mostly invisible | Yes | Best as server-derived receipt key inside the existing write transactions. No user flag or prompt. Current save already has duplicate checks at `save/dedup.ts` and request IDs in `memory-save.ts`, but no operation receipt table. |\n| 010/P2 T12 MCP tool-ownership map | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/index.ts`; `tools/memory-tools.ts`; `tools/context-tools.ts`; `tools/causal-tools.ts`; `tools/checkpoint-tools.ts`; `tools/lifecycle-tools.ts`; likely docs under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` or `references/memory/` | Doc + optional generated check | Low visibility | Yes | The 37-tool surface is already grouped by dispatcher modules. Ownership map should be generated or linted from `TOOL_NAMES` sets, not manually maintained. |\n| 010/P3 T13 stale/status hard-exclusion audit | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-health.ts`; `/doctor memory` surface | Audit/test + health/doctor diagnostic | Visible only as diagnostic | Yes | Current `memory_search` forces `includeArchived=false`, and FTS filters `importance_tier != 'deprecated'`. This needs an automatic audit that compares channels and reports whether default recall is silently excluding relevant deprecated/status rows. |\n| 002/T2 `source_kind` provenance + auto-cannot-overwrite-manual | `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-write-safety/spec.md`; `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`; `handlers/save/create-record.ts`; `handlers/memory-crud-update.ts`; `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`; `handlers/save/post-insert.ts`; constitutional rule surface `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/` | Spec amendment + schema + write guards + constitutional rule | Invisible except audit hints | Yes | `memory_index` currently has `provenance_source` / `provenance_actor`, but no `source_kind`. Auto/manual protection should be enforced on write paths, not by caller discipline. |\n| 002/T3 advisory near-duplicate | `.opencode/specs/.../002-memory-write-safety/spec.md`; `handlers/save/reconsolidation-bridge.ts`; `handlers/save/response-builder.ts`; optional `memory_index.near_duplicate_of` / `near_duplicate_similarity` in `vector-index-schema.ts` | Spec amendment + advisory response/audit, optional schema | Advisory, non-blocking | Yes | Existing assistive reconsolidation already classifies similarity tiers and logs shadow-only recommendations. Keep this deterministic and never hard-reject. |\n| 002/004/008 T11 automated-mutation audit | `lib/storage/mutation-ledger.ts`; `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts` governance/audit tables; `handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`; `handlers/memory-crud-update.ts`; `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts`; `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`; `lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts` | Schema/helper edit or reuse existing append-only ledger | Invisible, surfaced in diagnostics | Yes | Prefer extending existing `mutation_ledger` / `governance_audit` with `actor`, `operation`, and compact metadata over adding a parallel audit table unless query needs force it. |\n| 003/T14 explicit fingerprint design + `last_dedup_checked_at` | `.opencode/specs/.../003-incremental-index-foundation/spec.md`; `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`; `handlers/memory-index.ts`; planned `lib/storage/incremental-index.ts` / `canonical-fingerprint.ts` | Spec amendment + schema/indexing design | Invisible | Yes | Confirms existing 003 direction. Add the marker as self-maintaining scan metadata, not a user-run dedup command. |\n| 004/T7 first-timestamp-idempotent tombstone | `.opencode/specs/.../004-causal-edge-tombstones/spec.md`; `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`; planned `lib/causal/sweep.ts`; `handlers/memory-crud-delete.ts`; `handlers/memory-bulk-delete.ts`; `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`; `handlers/memory-crud-health.ts` | Spec amendment + schema/helper edit | Invisible, health-visible | Yes | Tombstone helper should use first timestamp semantics, so repeated cleanup does not extend retention or mutate audit history. |\n| 004/T8 active/purgeable partial-index split | `.opencode/specs/.../004-causal-edge-tombstones/spec.md`; `lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts`; `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts` | Spec amendment + schema/index edit | Invisible | Yes | For SQLite, adapt the guarantee with partial indexes over active and purgeable predicates. Pair with retention sweep and tombstone lookup paths. |\n| 004/005 T10 entity is not causal truth | `.opencode/specs/.../004-causal-edge-tombstones/spec.md`; `.opencode/specs/.../005-metadata-edge-promoter/spec.md`; `lib/extraction/entity-extractor.ts`; `handlers/causal-links-processor.ts`; `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`; constitutional rule surface | Spec amendment + invariant/constitutional rule | Invisible | Yes | Keep entity/co-occurrence as recall evidence only. Do not auto-promote entity links into `causal_edges` without explicit measured need. |\n| 005/T9 natural-key idempotent edge promotion + skip manual | `.opencode/specs/.../005-metadata-edge-promoter/spec.md`; `lib/storage/causal-edges.ts`; planned `lib/causal/frontmatter-promoter.ts`; `handlers/memory-index.ts`; `handlers/causal-links-processor.ts` | Spec amendment + storage helper edit | Invisible except warnings | Yes | `causal_edges` already has a natural unique key. The missing safety is that `insertEdge` currently updates `created_by` on existing rows, so auto promoters must skip manual rows. |\n| 006/T1 idempotency reconciliation cross-reference | `.opencode/specs/.../006-write-path-reconciliation/spec.md`; planned `lib/storage/statediff.ts`; `handlers/memory-save.ts`; `handlers/mutation-hooks.ts`; `handlers/save/enrichment-state.ts` | Spec amendment + design dependency | Invisible | Yes | Receipts should become the retry-safe write primitive before statediff subscribers increase retry/replay complexity. Async post-insert enrichment already matches the desired local pattern. |\n| 007/T13 stale-exclusion cross-reference | `.opencode/specs/.../007-semantic-trigger-fallback/spec.md`; `handlers/memory-search.ts`; `lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts`; `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`; `/doctor memory` | Spec amendment + audit coverage | Visible only as diagnostic | Yes | Add this as default-recall safety evidence for lexical-first/semantic fallback work. Avoid manual flags; health/doctor should report drift. |\n| 008/T4 scope reducers down to event-capture + diagnostics only | `.opencode/specs/.../008-learning-feedback-reducers/spec.md`; `008-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator/spec.md`; `003-causal-reducer/spec.md`; `004-retention-reducer/spec.md`; `005-env-tests-integration/spec.md`; `lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts`; `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts` | Major spec amendment + defer active modules | Low visibility | Yes | Current live ledger is already shadow-only and fail-safe. The active reducer children should be rescoped or deferred before implementation. |\n| 008/T5 reserve system feedback artifact types | `lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts`; `lib/feedback/query-flow-tracker.ts`; `mcp_server/context-server.ts`; `schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts` | Schema/type edit + validation | Invisible | Yes | Feedback event types are currently internal. Keep them unforgeable by not exposing a user-writable event tool; if a tool exists later, validate `source_kind=system` server-side. |\n| 008/T6 symmetric damping + rare/constitutional immunity | `008-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer/spec.md`; `004-retention-reducer/spec.md`; `lib/feedback/batch-learning.ts`; `lib/governance/memory-retention-sweep.ts`; `lib/scoring/importance-tiers.ts`; constitutional rule surface | Spec amendment + reducer invariant + constitutional rule | Invisible, diagnostic-only | Yes | If reducers are reintroduced later, use symmetric soft accumulation and hard immunity for constitutional/critical/user-confirmed sparse-domain records. No one-off demotion from a single negative signal. |\n\n## Integration sequence\n\n1. Amend `008` first because it prevents building the wrong thing. The current `008` parent and children still plan active causal and retention consumers; MemClaw evidence says the safe v1 is event capture plus diagnostics only.\n\n2. Amend `002` provenance next. `source_kind`, manual/constitutional overwrite guards, and automated-mutation audit are prerequisites for every later automated writer.\n\n3. Add 010/P1 idempotency receipts before broader reconciliation. `memory_save` and `memory_update` are retryable write surfaces today, and 006 statediff/replay will make idempotency more important.\n\n4. Align 006 with the receipt primitive and async enrichment. This keeps retry/replay semantics explicit before statediff subscribers move mutation hooks out of handlers.\n\n5. Amend 004 tombstones and indexes. Causal cleanup should be idempotent and audit-preserving before generated edge volume grows.\n\n6. Amend 005 edge promotion. Natural-key upsert plus skip-manual is safe only after 002 manual protection and 004 cleanup semantics are settled.\n\n7. Add 010/P3 and 007 stale/status audit. This is independent enough to run early, but it is most useful once status/tombstone semantics are explicit.\n\n8. Add 010/P2 tool-ownership map. It is low-risk and can land anytime, but dependency-wise it should read the current dispatcher modules and stay generated/linted.\n\n9. Confirm 003/T14 during 003 implementation. It mostly validates the existing 003 design, with `last_dedup_checked_at` as an incremental marker.\n\n10. Add constitutional rules last only after wording is stable. The durable rules should be narrow: no automated overwrite of manual/constitutional state, entity evidence is not causal truth, and feedback cannot demote protected memory.\n\n## UX + automation hooks per item\n\n| Item | Automatic trigger | UX touchpoint |\n|---|---|---|\n| 010/P1 idempotency receipts | On every `memory_save` / `memory_update`, derive receipt key from operation + content/request fingerprint inside the DB transaction. | No prompt, no flag. Identical retry returns the prior success envelope with a small `idempotentReplay:true` metadata field only if trace/details are shown. |\n| 002/T2 source_kind guard | On every write path, set `source_kind` server-side from caller/path/tool context and reject or skip automated overwrites of manual/constitutional fields. | No user setup. Only noisy case is a clear warning in response hints when an automated mutation was skipped to preserve manual data. |\n| 002/T3 near-duplicate advisory | During save-time reconsolidation when embeddings already exist, compute deterministic similarity and attach advisory metadata. | Non-blocking hint only. No review queue, no LLM judge, no “approve duplicate?” prompt. |\n| T11 automated-mutation audit | Append compact rows automatically from mutation hooks, retention sweep, causal promotion, tombstone cleanup, and reducer diagnostics. | Surfaced through `memory_health`, `memory_stats`, or `/doctor memory` summaries, not normal responses unless something fails. |\n| 010/P3 stale/status audit | `memory_health` / `/doctor memory` runs channel comparison checks for deprecated/status rows and reports hard-exclusion drift. | Diagnostic only. Default search stays simple; audit says whether recall risk exists and where. |\n| 008/T4 event-capture only | Existing `feedback-ledger.ts` continues to log search/citation/follow-on events shadow-only; reducer children become diagnostics/replay only. | Zero-friction. No user-facing feedback controls until measured quality justifies a live reducer. |\n| 008/T5 reserved feedback types | Feedback event source/type is stamped by server internals in `context-server.ts` and `query-flow-tracker.ts`; user-provided event writes are not accepted. | No visible UX unless a malicious/manual call is rejected with a concise “system feedback type is reserved” error. |\n| 008/T6 constitutional immunity | Any future reducer/sweep checks `importance_tier`, constitutional path, pinned state, and source kind before demotion/delete decisions. | Protected records simply stay protected. Diagnostics can explain “skipped due to constitutional/critical immunity” without prompting. |\n\nDELTA_JSON: {\"iteration\":\"001\",\"focus\":\"integration surface & sequencing map\",\"findingsCount\":16,\"newInfoRatio\":0.78,\"impacts\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts <- T1 idempotency receipts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts <- T1 idempotency receipts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts <- T1/T2/T7/T8/T14 schema additions\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/causal-edges.ts <- T2/T7/T9 manual-safe edge mutation\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts <- T4/T5 feedback event capture only\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/spec.md <- T4/T5/T6 scope-down\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts <- T13 stale/status hard-exclusion audit\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/index.ts <- T12 tool ownership map\"],\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/research.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-write-safety/spec.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/003-incremental-index-foundation/spec.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/004-causal-edge-tombstones/spec.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-metadata-edge-promoter/spec.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/006-write-path-reconciliation/spec.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/007-semantic-trigger-fallback/spec.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/008-learning-feedback-reducers/spec.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-update.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/causal-edges.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/index.ts\"]}","time":{"start":1780738367010,"end":1780738430617},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06931e4fb7bebe7f016a23e93f00288191804f0d55e5826bf7","phase":"final_ans